# Build-context hygiene (PB-4): the Dockerfile does `COPY . .`, so without this
# file whatever the host happens to have leaks into the image — a local
# node_modules overwrites the `npm ci` layer file-by-file (wrong-platform
# binaries) and makes the context transfer pathologically slow, and stale build
# output or local env files ship along with it. Keep host-generated and
# secret-bearing paths out of the build context. CI plants a sentinel in
# node_modules and asserts the built image does not contain it.
node_modules
.next
.swc
coverage
tsconfig.tsbuildinfo
npm-debug.log*
.env*
data
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
